wikipedia_page.main: Clifton "Cliff" Chadwick (26 January 1914 – 8 March 1999) was an footballer who scored 45 goals from 174 appearances in the Football League playing as a winger for Oldham Athletic, Middlesbrough, Hull City and Darlington in the 1930s and 1940s. He went on to be player-manager of Stockton.
